title: Jelsa, Norway
text:
Jelsa is a village in <a href="Suldal">Suldal</a> municipality in <a href="Rogaland">Rogaland</a> county, <a href="Norway">Norway</a>. The village is located along the inner part of the <a href="Boknafjorden">Boknafjorden</a>, near the mouths of the <a href="Sandsfjorden">Sandsfjorden</a> and <a href="Erfjorden">Erfjorden</a>. The village is the site of a school, store, gas station, and some small stores. There was a barrel factory here until it closed in 2009. <a href="Jelsa%20Church">Jelsa Church</a> is located in this village.
The village was the <a href="administrative%20centre">administrative centre</a> of the old municipality of <a href="Jelsa%20%28municipality%29">Jelsa</a> which existed from 1838 until 1965.
The village lies along <a href="Norwegian%20county%20road">Norwegian county road</a> 517, and it is a regular ferry stop on the route from <a href="Nedstrand">Nedstrand</a>-<a href="Hebnes">Hebnes</a>-<a href="Fold%C3%B8y%20%28Rogaland%29">Foldøy</a>-Jelsa.
